The paper discusses a novel technique for automatic program repair, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The technique involves identifying sets of similar code that are expected to undergo similar changes, which requires code analysis and similarity analysis, falling under programming languages (cs.PL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of test-suite spectrum and revision history, which are related to machine learning (cs.LG) and cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-categories, respectively.
